<H2><A NAME="SECTION0211270000000000000000">
3.1.27 IsAromatic</A>
</H2>
<dl><dd><pre class="verbatim">
virtual bool IsAromatic() const
</pre></dl>

<P>
Return the Boolean aromatic property of an atom.  The default value is
false.  The aromatic property of an atom can be set using the
<code>OEAtomBase::SetAromatic</code> method.  The aromatic properties of atoms
and bonds in a molecule are typically set by calling either the OEChem
<code>OEAssignAromaticFlags</code> function, or possibly the
<code>OEClearAromaticFlags</code> function.

<P>

